title: For Sale:  Colt Government Auto .380 Stainless
postcontent:
This Colt MK IV/Series 80 Government Model 380 semi-automatic is in excellent condition. I am the original owner, have run < 100 rounds through it, and have kept it clean and appropriately lubricated. This pistol is a scaled-down version of the famous Colt 1911 model and, except for the reduced dimensions, is nearly identical in appearance and function. This is a great, easy-to-conceal Colt and has just the right combination of weight, balance, sight size, barrel length and grip length to be easy and comfortable to shoot. I have shot a variety of ball and hollow-point ammunition and never experienced a jam or misfire.

This Govt model Colt had a very short manufacturing window and is thus becoming more and more difficult to find. It has emerged as a genuine collectible. Other specks include a 3.25" barrel, black original Colt grips, original box and all paperwork that was packaged by Colt.

I'll be happy to throw in two compatible holsters. One is a injected-molded, high density plastic Fobus BS-2 paddle holster and the other a nylon-constructed Hafner clip holster.

The market range for these pistols are $700 - $950 ... and, again, the gun is in exceptional condition, I am the original owner, it is a low-use weapon, I'm offering it with the original box and paperwork, and am throwing in the two holsters.  

Thanks!

The pump includes an under Picatinny rail for the mounting of a forward grip, or a light or laser. The included top Picatinny sight rail will accept many types of optics or iron sights. Forward and rear sling loops are built in, and a basic sling is included. The soft rubber butt pad helps to tame recoil.

title: For Sale:  Daniel Defense upper .300 blackout w/ 920 rds ammo
postcontent:
I have a like new Daniel Defense DDM4 V7 complete upper receiver in .300 blackout for sale.  It has only been fired on two range trips for a total of 80 rounds and cleaned well after each trip.  I also added a nice compensator to it made right here inTucson from Black weapons armory X-Comp.  It works really well.  http://www.blackweaponsarmory.com/bwa-x-comps/bwa-x-comp-308-7-62-compensator-5-8-x-24-thread.html   Is the link to the 7.62 comp if you want to check it out.  I also have 920 rounds of 147 grain ammo to go with it.  All you need is any normal 5.56/223 lower, attach the upper and you are set.  It uses normal 5.56 mags...only difference is the barrell and of course, the extra power you get from .300 blackout (7.62 x 35).  You can use this to hunt hog, deer, etc... too.  This was part ofthe reason I bought it, but since I have yet to go hunting after owning this gun for a year, I doubt I will go anytime soon.  

If you are not familiar with .300 blackout, do some research and watch Travis Haley's youtube video on the year of the .300 blackout http://m.youtube.com/watch?v=tgKjbySsAik  
This thing will last...after all, it is Daniel Defense.
Overall, selling the ammo for about .76 cents/round which is a pretty good rate plus $850 for the upper with the (cost me $120 plus tax)X-compensator on it.  Thanks for looking.
Note that sight does not come with upper.  It also does come with the never opened rail pieces you can place where ever gou want on the modular float rail.
Not particularly looking for a trade, but you can always offer me something I can't refuse.

title: For Sale:  Colt AR-15 Rifle Pre-ban SP1 Receiver 30 Rd Mag
location: north dakota, North Dakota, United States
postcontent:
This is a Pre-ban Colt AR15 with an SP1 Receiver. This is the 1st civilian version of the military M16 to be issued to the public. It is in really good condition and will make someone a great trophy gun. It is in great firing condition and has not been fired since 1995. It has spent it's life in a gun safe ever since. Everyone that see's it in our store thinks that it is a fully automatic M16 and no one wants the newer AR15 after seeing it's past in this one. It is known for it's triangular hand guard and bayonet lug and some other features listed below. The features below were shared with the M16. 

Slickside The earliest version of the AR-15 upper receiver which can easily be identified by its lack of forward assist and brass deflector. This type of receiver was used on the original M16, USAF weapons, and the SP1 civilian rifle. 

The bayonet lug on AR-15 rifles is a small protrusion on the front underside of the gas block. This is present on the majority of Colt AR-15 military rifles, but is omitted in the case of some carbines as it is redundant due to the bayonet requiring a longer barrel to be mounted onto. It is also absent from a number of civilian rifles, most notably the Match Target rifles, in order to comply with various laws and regulations. 

The iconic M16 flash hider often referred to as the “Birdcage”, and was on a closed design to address problems encountered with the duckbill type flash hiders snagging on vegetation. Introduced on the M16A1, it has 6 ports equally distributed around the flash hider. 

Shipping is $30 and that includes Insurance on the gun. It is a great rifle that you can be proud of. If you are a Vietnam Vet then this will look very familiar to you and bring back some memories of the past.

title: For Sale:  Colt AR-15 Rifle Pre-ban SP1 Receiver 30 Rd Mag
location: new york, New York, United States
postcontent:
This is a Pre-ban Colt AR15 with an SP1 Receiver. This is the 1st civilian version of the military M16 to be issued to the public. It is in really good condition and will make someone a great trophy gun. It is in great firing condition and has not been fired since 1995. It has spent it's life in a gun safe ever since. Everyone that see's it in our store thinks that it is a fully automatic M16 and no one wants the newer AR15 after seeing it's past in this one. It is known for it's triangular hand guard and bayonet lug and some other features listed below. The features below were shared with the M16. 

Slickside The earliest version of the AR-15 upper receiver which can easily be identified by its lack of forward assist and brass deflector. This type of receiver was used on the original M16, USAF weapons, and the SP1 civilian rifle. 

The bayonet lug on AR-15 rifles is a small protrusion on the front underside of the gas block. This is present on the majority of Colt AR-15 military rifles, but is omitted in the case of some carbines as it is redundant due to the bayonet requiring a longer barrel to be mounted onto. It is also absent from a number of civilian rifles, most notably the Match Target rifles, in order to comply with various laws and regulations. 

The iconic M16 flash hider often referred to as the “Birdcage”, and was on a closed design to address problems encountered with the duckbill type flash hiders snagging on vegetation. Introduced on the M16A1, it has 6 ports equally distributed around the flash hider. 

Shipping is $30 and that includes Insurance on the gun. It is a great rifle that you can be proud of. If you are a Vietnam Vet then this will look very familiar to you and bring back some memories of the past.

title: For Sale:  Colt AR-15 Rifle Pre-ban SP1 Receiver 30 Rd Mag
location: new york, New York, United States
postcontent:
This is a Pre-ban Colt AR15 with an SP1 Receiver. This is the 1st civilian version of the military M16 to be issued to the public. It is in really good condition and will make someone a great trophy gun. It is in great firing condition and has not been fired since 1995. It has spent it's life in a gun safe ever since. Everyone that see's it in our store thinks that it is a fully automatic M16 and no one wants the newer AR15 after seeing it's past in this one. It is known for it's triangular hand guard and bayonet lug and some other features listed below. The features below were shared with the M16. 

Slickside The earliest version of the AR-15 upper receiver which can easily be identified by its lack of forward assist and brass deflector. This type of receiver was used on the original M16, USAF weapons, and the SP1 civilian rifle. 

The bayonet lug on AR-15 rifles is a small protrusion on the front underside of the gas block. This is present on the majority of Colt AR-15 military rifles, but is omitted in the case of some carbines as it is redundant due to the bayonet requiring a longer barrel to be mounted onto. It is also absent from a number of civilian rifles, most notably the Match Target rifles, in order to comply with various laws and regulations. 

The iconic M16 flash hider often referred to as the “Birdcage”, and was on a closed design to address problems encountered with the duckbill type flash hiders snagging on vegetation. Introduced on the M16A1, it has 6 ports equally distributed around the flash hider. 

Shipping is $30 and that includes Insurance on the gun. It is a great rifle that you can be proud of. If you are a Vietnam Vet then this will look very familiar to you and bring back some memories of the past.
